Phạm Nhật Tuyên is an Intern AI Intern with 0 years of commercial experience, focusing on academic and project-based applications of Artificial Intelligence. Their core expertise lies in Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing (NLP), and Image Processing, with practical experience in developing models based on Transformer architectures, Linear Regression, Random Forest, and Decision Tree algorithms. They are adept at techniques such as data preprocessing, tokenization, embedding, classification, sequence-to-sequence modeling, fine-tuning, and OCR, with a focus on evaluating performance using metrics like ROUGE. Notable academic projects include developing an ID Card Recognition system utilizing Machine Learning, Image Processing, and OCR for information extraction and preprocessing pipeline design. They also built an NLP model for Text Summarization, incorporating tokenization and stopword removal, evaluated with ROUGE metrics. Furthermore, they engineered a Weather Prediction model, comparing various predictive algorithms including Linear Regression, Random Forest Regressor/Classifier, and Decision Tree Regressor.
Technically, they are proficient in Python, Java, C, and JavaScript, and have hands-on experience with frameworks like Node.js, SpringBoot, and Angular. Database skills include MySQL and MongoDB. They are familiar with cloud services like Firebase and leverage tools such as GitHub for version control and Kaggle for data science competitions. Academically, they are pursuing a Bachelor's in Computer Science and possess Intermediate (B1) English proficiency, evidenced by a Cambridge English B1 Preliminary certification.